# gen178 — B5 bounded loops: parrot0 executes a `while` accumulator over the
# local environment, with a step ceiling so a non-terminating loop is refused
# rather than hung. Covers real iterative functions (sum, factorial).
#expect: pass
#faculty: symeval-loops
> what does sum(4) return: int sum(int n) { int s = 0; int i = 1; while (i <= n) { s = s + i; i = i + 1; } return s; }
< sum(4) returns 10
> what does fact(5) return: int fact(int n) { int r = 1; while (n > 1) { r = r * n; n = n - 1; } return r; }
< fact(5) returns 120
> what does sum(0) return: int sum(int n) { int s = 0; int i = 1; while (i <= n) { s = s + i; i = i + 1; } return s; }
< sum(0) returns 0
